layer.title: Overarching goals
layer.annotation: Goal: Prepare system for installing packages Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult
Goal: Obtain, build, and test the latest source distribution of GNU `help2man`. Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult
Goal: Dump this shell's history to the terminal and a file at the path "/herstory" Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult

layer.title: Individual commands
layer.annotation: Goal: Pick an Alpine mirror for the `apk` package manager to use, and enable the community repository. Tools: Busybox's built-in Borne shell interpreter runs Alpine's `setup-apkrepos` script. Result: successResult
Goal: Change working directory to the current shell account's `HOME` Tool: The cd builtin to the shell interpreter included with the BusyBox multi-call binary Result: successResult

Goal: List the contents of the root directory of the running system. Tool: The `ls` tool included with the BusyBox multi-call binary Mistake: This command is completely superfluous, because it does nothing to further the overall goal of this session. Result: successResult
Download the 1.49.3 release of the GNU `help2man` source distribution from their archive server. Tool: GNU `wget` Result: successResult

Goal: Extract the newly-downloaded `help2man` source distribution tarball. Tool: the `tar` tool included with the BusyBox multi-call binary Mistakes: Operator uses the `-z` flag that decompresses Gzip archives, but this is a xz-compressed archive. Result: successFailure
Goal: Extract the newly-downloaded `help2man` source distribution tarball. Tool: the `tar` tool included with the BusyBox multi-call binary Result: successResult
Goal: Change working directories to the root of the newly-extracted `help2man` archive. Tool: The Busybox shell's `cd` builtin. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the `help2man` source distribution for building. Tool: The BusyBox shell interpreter running the `configure` script. Discovery: Perl 5.8 or greater is required to configure the `help2man` source distribution. Result: successFailure

Goal: Install Perl from Alpine's package archive servers Tool: The Alpine `apk` package manager's `add` command. Mistakes: The letter `d` is typed one to many times in the argument `add`before it is corrected. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the `help2man` source distribution for building. Tool: The BusyBox shell interpreter running the `configure` script. Discovery: A C compiler is required to configure the `help2man` source distribution. Result: successFailure

Goal: Install the GNU C Compiler Collection and C standard library headers from the Alpine package repositories. Tool: The `apk` package manager included with Alpine running its `add` subcommand. Result: successResult
Goal: Configure the `help2man` source distribution for building Tool: The source distribution's included `configure` script ran by BusyBox's shell interpreter. Result: successResult
Goal: Build the newly-configured `help2man` source distribution. Tools: An invokation of a `make` command. Discovery: No `make` command is installed yet. Result: successFailure
Goal: Install the GNU Make build system from Alpine's package archive servers. Tool: Alpine's `apk` package manager's `add` subcommand. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the `help2man` source distribution for building Tool: The source distribution's included `configure` script ran by BusyBox's shell interpreter. Mistakes: `make` is typed into the command line before the operator decides to backspace and rerun `configure` instead. Result: successResult
Goal: Build the `help2man` tool from source distribution. Tool: GNU `make` running the makefile generated by `configure`. Result: successResult

Goal: Install the `help2man` tool to the `configure`d `PREFIX`. Tool: GNU `make` running the `install` target. Mistake: The `n` in `install` is typed once, erased, and typed again. Result: successResult

Goal: Check that the version of the installed `help2man` tool is the one that we expect. Tool: The `help2man` tool with its `--version` flag Mistake: `help1` is typed before erasing the errant `1` and finishing the word `help2man`. Result: successResult
Goal: Verify that `help2man` tool in the `PATH` is installed in the expected `PREFIX`. The `which` command included in the BusyBox multi-call binary. Result: successResult

Goal: Dump the shell's history to a file named `herstory` in the system's root directory (`/`). Tool: The BusyBox shell interpreter's `history` builtin Mistake: `tee` is typed at the beginning of the command line before it is erased and the full command is typed instead. Result: successResult
